NUVIO WIZARD DESIGN PRINCIPLES (MANDATORY)

All wizards in Nuvio MUST use the WizardShell component and follow these principles without exception.

---

## THE WIZARDSHELL RULE

Every full-screen wizard MUST use:
  import { WizardShell, useWizardAnimation } from '@/components/wizard-shell';

NEVER build a wizard with raw `fixed inset-0 z-50\` divs, local StepDots, or inline animation state.

WizardShell handles all of:
- Full-screen overlay with correct sidebar offset (`left: var(--sidebar-offset-global, 0px)`)
- Gradient background with smooth transition between steps
- Fade-in on mount (via `visible\` state)
- Step dots in top bar
- Back button (ChevronLeft, bordered white pill)
- Close/skip button (X icon, bordered white pill)
- Content fade + slide animation between steps (220ms)
- Safe area insets (iOS notch, mobile nav bar)

Usage pattern:
```tsx
const { animating, direction, animate } = useWizardAnimation();
const [step, setStep] = useState(0);
const [visible, setVisible] = useState(false);

useEffect(() => {
  const t = setTimeout(() => setVisible(true), 30);
  return () => clearTimeout(t);
}, []);

function next() { animate('forward', () => setStep(s => s + 1)); }
function back() { animate('back', () => setStep(s => s - 1)); }

return (
  <WizardShell
    gradient={STEP_GRADIENTS[step]}
    visible={visible}
    step={step}
    totalSteps={TOTAL_STEPS}
    showBack={step > 0}
    showClose={true}
    onBack={back}
    onClose={onDismiss}
    animating={animating}
    direction={direction}
  >
    {step === 0 && <StepZero />}
    {step === 1 && <StepOne />}
    <div className="pt-6">
      <button onClick={next}>Fortsæt</button>
    </div>
  </WizardShell>
);
```

