## WIZARD UX PRINCIPLES

### Structure
Every wizard MUST follow this step structure:
1. **Intro / Context step** — WHY is this wizard needed? What will the user get from it?
2. **Input steps** — One topic per step. Never combine multiple inputs on one step.
3. **Confirmation step** — Show what will be saved. Let user verify before committing.

### Progressive Disclosure
- Reveal only what the user needs NOW
- Never show all inputs at once
- Use the step count (max 6 steps) as a forcing function for simplicity

### Honest Tone
- Explain WHY before asking for input
- Reinforce that accuracy matters
- Use microcopy that builds trust: "Jo mere præcist, jo bedre"
- Avoid demanding language — invite, don't interrogate

### Microcopy Standards
Step label (above headline):
```tsx
<p className="text-[11px] font-semibold uppercase tracking-widest text-emerald-600/70">
  Kategori
</p>
```

Headline:
```tsx
<h2 className="text-3xl sm:text-4xl font-bold leading-tight tracking-tight mb-3">
  Hvad vil du opnå?
</h2>
```

Body/description:
```tsx
<p className="text-foreground/60 text-base leading-relaxed mb-6">
  Brug det som en guide, ikke en dom.
</p>
```

